---
import { getBrand, siteConfig } from "../../site-config";

function hostnameForBrand(astroHost: string): string {
  if (astroHost) return astroHost;
  try {
    return new URL(siteConfig.canonicalOrigin).hostname;
  } catch {
    return "";
  }
}

const brand = getBrand(hostnameForBrand(Astro.url.hostname));
const phone = siteConfig.phoneDisplay;
const tel = siteConfig.phoneE164;
---

<h1>Terms of Service</h1>
<p class="legal-updated"><strong>Last updated:</strong> May 30, 2026</p>

<div class="legal-disclaimer-box">
  <strong>Disclaimer — informational use only</strong>
  This website and its service-area pages are provided for <strong>general information and intake
  coordination only</strong>. Content—including market anchors, stress or risk indexes, charts, USGS or
  other public-data references, calculators, reviews or job-count displays, and scheduling language—is{" "}
  <strong>illustrative and educational</strong>. It is <strong>not</strong> a licensed contractor
  estimate, engineering report, structural inspection, insurance determination, appraisal, or government
  hazard map. Obtain <strong>on-site evaluation by qualified professionals</strong> before making repair,
  purchase, or insurance decisions. We do not guarantee accuracy of third-party or page-local composite
  data.
</div>

<h2>1. Acceptance</h2>
<p>By using this website or calling our phone numbers, you agree to these Terms of Service.</p>

<h2>2. What we provide</h2>
<p>
  {brand.name} provides <strong>information, intake, and scheduling coordination</strong> for residential
  home services. We connect callers with <strong>independent licensed and insured contractors or partners</strong>{" "}
  where available.
</p>
<p>We do <strong>not</strong> guarantee:</p>
<ul>
  <li>same-day or emergency arrival times</li>
  <li>a specific price, quote, or &ldquo;starting at&rdquo; rate unless confirmed during intake or on a work order</li>
  <li>availability in every ZIP code at all hours</li>
  <li>outcomes based on illustrative indexes, calculators, or third-party benchmarks shown on the site</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Not an emergency services agency</h2>
<p>
  For life-threatening emergencies (fire, gas leak, immediate medical danger), contact <strong>911</strong>{" "}
  or your utility emergency line first.
</p>

<h2>4. Pricing and payment</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Diagnostic, trip, after-hours, and repair charges vary by market and scope</li>
  <li>Any price mentioned on marketing pages is <strong>illustrative</strong> unless confirmed during intake</li>
  <li>Payment terms are between you and the performing contractor unless we state otherwise on the call</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Third-party contractors</h2>
<p>
  Contractors are independent businesses. We are not responsible for their workmanship, warranties, or
  conduct, except as required by applicable law.
</p>

<h2>6. Website content and data displays</h2>
<p>
  Market anchors, stress indexes, maps, trend lines, partner logos, and educational blocks are{" "}
  <strong>informational only</strong>. References to public datasets (including terrain or infrastructure
  context) are not site-specific engineering certifications.
</p>

<h2>7. Reviews and social proof</h2>
<p>
  Ratings or job counts shown on service-area pages may be <strong>aggregated or illustrative</strong> for
  scheduling context. They are not a guarantee of future results for your specific property.
</p>

<h2>8. Acceptable use</h2>
<p>You agree not to misuse the site, submit false requests, or use automated means to scrape or disrupt services.</p>

<h2>9. Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
<p>
  The site and coordination services are provided <strong>&ldquo;as is&rdquo;</strong> to the fullest extent
  permitted by law.
</p>

<h2>10. Limitation of liability</h2>
<p>
  To the fullest extent permitted by law, we are not liable for indirect, incidental, or consequential
  damages arising from use of the site or services coordinated through it.
</p>

<h2>11. Governing law</h2>
<p>
  These Terms are governed by the laws of the <strong>State of Maine</strong>, without regard to
  conflict-of-law rules, except where consumer protection laws in your state require otherwise.
</p>

<h2>12. Contact</h2>
<p>
  {brand.name}<br />
  Phone: <a href={`tel:${tel.replace(/^\+/, "")}`}>{phone}</a><br />
  Website: {siteConfig.canonicalOrigin}
</p>
